    \begin {tikzcd}
      Gz\ar [r, hook]\ar [d, "Gf"'] & C(z, x)\ar [d, "f^*"] \\
      Gz'\ar [r, hook] & C(z', x)
    \end {tikzcd}


 commutes, so that for m\in  Gz, f^*m = fm \in  Gz'. Thus the disjoint
  union of the Gz is a sieve. Conversely, given a sieve S, we
  define Gz = \{z\xrightarrow {m} x\in  C(z, x)\}, with action on morphisms by
  pre-composition.

A subobject of an object x in a category C is a
monomorphism with codomain x, ordered by subobject
inclusion 




